Since 2011, Global Citizen claims to have recorded more than 19 million “actions” from its supporters in favor of a large number of diverse goals.
Thanks to these actions, they claim to have managed to get world leaders to announce commitments and policies worth more than $37 billion, which will impact the lives of more than 2,250 million people in 2030.
